(48, 'activity', 'Speed Summits', 'Speed Summits  is an innovative program for safer, faster climbing.', 'activity-trip-list', 'trial-running', '1724337126.jpg', '172468180942.jpg', 'Speed summits is a unique pre-acclimatization program developed for for the reduction of  expeditions duration.', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Speed summits is a unique pre-acclimatization program developed for for the reduction of  expeditions duration. Rapid speed summits teams spend 30 to 50% less time away from home and arrive at base camp well-rested, energized, and prepared to take full advantage of every weather window. Acclimatization for this expedition is already done at home. While a  normal expeditions takes two months, our speed summits Expedition saves time and additionally increases safety and chances of success in a short period of time .</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This special kind of pre-expedition preparation, combined with our small group sizes, maximum oxygen support, the latest equipment, an experienced team of climbing Sherpas who have stood on the summit of Mount Everest  several times and our vast  experience in the climbing industry allow us to schedule the expedition at a short period of time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What is speed summits ? <br>Pre-acclimatization<br>With speed summits , acclimatization starts long before you get to the mountain. First, we deliver a hypoxic tent and training gear directly to your doorstep. Combined with carefully fine-tuned training regimens, this technology can get you adjusted to altitudes of 17,000 to 19,000 feet in just four to eight weeks. As soon as your body is ready, we trigger a cascade of precisely choreographed logistics to get you to base camp as fast as possible. Layers of failsafes and backups ensure that there are no hiccups. All this allows us to run expeditions to the world’s highest peaks in just 30 to 35 days—rather than 50 or 60.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">HIGHLIGHTS:<br>*Reduced expedition duration (3 weeks only) due to pre-acclimatization<br>*2:1 Sherpa client ratio on summit day<br>*Unlimited oxygen* for each climber<br>*Spare oxygen system for each climber<br>*IFMGA &amp; Expert Sherpas lead guide <br>*Small group size for increased safety and higher success rate</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Comming soon', 'Speed Summits \r\n\r\nSpeed Summits  is an innovative program for safer, faster climbing.\r\n\r\nSpeed summits is a unique pre-acclimatization program developed for for the reduction of  expeditions duration. Rapid speed summits teams spend 30 to 50% less time away from home and arrive at base camp well-rested, energized, and prepared to take full advantage of every weather window. Acclimatization for this expedition is already done at home. While a  normal expeditions takes two months, our speed summits Expedition saves time and additionally increases safety and chances of success in a short period of time .\r\n\r\nThis special kind of pre-expedition preparation, combined with our small group sizes, maximum oxygen support, the latest equipment, an experienced team of climbing Sherpas who have stood on the summit of Mount Everest  several times and our vast  experience in the climbing industry allow us to schedule the expedition at a short period of time. \r\n\r\n \r\nWhat is speed summits ? \r\nPre-acclimatization\r\nWith speed summits , acclimatization starts long before you get to the mountain. First, we deliver a hypoxic tent and training gear directly to your doorstep. Combined with carefully fine-tuned training regimens, this technology can get you adjusted to altitudes of 17,000 to 19,000 feet in just four to eight weeks. As soon as your body is ready, we trigger a cascade of precisely choreographed logistics to get you to base camp as fast as possible. Layers of failsafes and backups ensure that there are no hiccups. All this allows us to run expeditions to the world’s highest peaks in just 30 to 35 days—rather than 50 or 60.\r\n\r\nHIGHLIGHTS:\r\n*Reduced expedition duration (3 weeks only) due to pre-acclimatization\r\n*2:1 Sherpa client ratio on summit day\r\n*Unlimited oxygen* for each climber\r\n*Spare oxygen system for each climber\r\n*IFMGA & Expert Sherpas lead guide \r\n*Small group size for increased safety and higher success rate', '10', '0', NULL, '2024-02-06 11:50:45', '2024-08-27 06:04:48'),
(49, 'activity', 'Sking', 'Dream of all adventure skiers in the Nepal\'s himalays .', 'activity-trip-list', 'sking', '1724680932.png', '172468105223.png', 'Experience the Himalayas on skis, the ultimate way to experience this mountain range that includes high altitude trekking, mountain peak climbing, and skiing at one go', '<p>Experience the Himalayas on skis, the ultimate way to experience this mountain range that includes high altitude trekking, mountain peak climbing, and skiing at one go.Nepal brings out the best skiing and mountaineering expeditions. The great heights and wide stretch of Himalayas make it a fun full adventure. Skiing in Nepal on the snowy mountain and, the charismatic weather makes it an adventurous sport. People from within Nepal and other tourists visit the place to enjoy the pleasure of skiing.</p>\r\n<p>Skiing in Nepal <br>Nepal brings out the best skiing and mountaineering expeditions. The great heights and wide stretch of Himalayas make it a fun full adventure. Skiing in Nepal on the snowy mountain and, the charismatic weather makes it an adventurous sport. People from within Nepal and other tourists visit the place to enjoy the pleasure of skiing.</p>\r\n<p>Nepal, being home to eight of the highest mountains in the world, really brings out the best of skiing voyages. The Everest region, Dhaulagiri, Makalu, Cho Oyu, Annapurna, Dolpo regions, Kangchenjunga, all sit ready for you to explore. Nepal has so much to offer that it would take a lifetime for you to ski the same place twice! </p>\r\n<p><br>We operate our Ski Expeditions in April (Nepal spring) and October (Nepal autumn). Whilst the weather during both of these seasons is generally stable, our pick is October for a couple of reasons. Firstly, there’s a lot more snow on the ground post-monsoon than pre-monsoon. This translates to more reliable skiing conditions and less crevasses. Less crevasses is always good! The weather is getting cooler as winter approaches which equals crisp clear days high up.</p>\r\n<p>Skiing in the Nepal’s  Himalayas is one of the best ways to get thrilling experiences. Skiing in Himalayan might be dream for every adventurous Skier. It is high altitude trek combined with skiing, mountaineering and trekking .</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '0', NULL, '2024-07-15 10:40:17', '2024-08-27 14:54:42'),
