Diary</li>\r\n<li>Pocket knife</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Hygiene and first aid</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Skincare (Maximum SPF sunscreen and lip balm)</li>\r\n<li>Toothbrush, Toothpaste, Soap, Moisturizer</li>\r\n<li>Hand Sanitizer</li>\r\n<li>Toilet paper and wet wipes</li>\r\n<li>Personal first aid kit (Include personal prescriptions, high altitude medications, painkillers, first-aid tape, band-aids etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Water treatment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Others</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Comfort Foods (Bring snacks and foods you like to munch)</li>\r\n<li>Travel clothes to wear in Kathmandu</li>\r\n<li>Sleeping bag (-20 degrees sleeping bag)</li>\r\n<li>Inflatable mattress</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Ski Packing List</strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>There’s nothing worse than leaving your ski holiday packing to the last minute and drowning in a pile of gloves, socks and thermals the night before you leave. Take your time and go through our useful guide for snowsports essentials to help make sure you’ve got everything you need in your bag.</p>\r\n<p>The golden rule of ski holiday preparation is clever packing. We’ve all been there… stuck at the top of a lift on the coldest day having left behind a crucial piece of clothing or kit. If you have a history of poor packing, we’ve created a fail-safe packing list to make sure you bring everything you need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>  Travel Essentials</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tickets, travel money, passport</li>\r\n<li>Flight/train/ferry/coach/transfer details</li>\r\n<li>Holiday/accommodation/ski hire details</li>\r\n<li>Insurance details</li>\r\n<li>Fully charged mobile phone, charger and external battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Ski/Snowboard Equipment</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ski boots/snowboard boots</li>\r\n<li>Skis/snowboard (in ski bag)</li>\r\n<li>Poles</li>\r\n<li>Day rucksack</li>\r\n<li>Helmet</li>\r\n<li>Transceiver, shovel and probe (for staying safe off piste)</li>\r\n<li>Water bottle or Camelbak</li>\r\n<li>Multitool for repairs or adjustments on the go</li>\r\n<li>Ski Goggles</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Ski/Snowboard Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Warm hat/beanie</li>\r\n<li>Sunglasses</li>\r\n<li>Neck warmer/buff</li>\r\n<li>2x thermal tops</li>\r\n<li>2x fleeces</li>\r\n<li>Waterproof ski jacket</li>\r\n<li>Waterproof ski trousers</li>\r\n<li>Waterproof gloves or mittens</li>\r\n<li>Thermal bottoms</li>\r\n<li>2 or 3 pairs of ski/board socks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Other Clothes</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jeans/long trousers</li>\r\n<li>T-shirts/tops</li>\r\n<li>Jumper or fleece</li>\r\n<li>Underwear including socks</li>\r\n<li>Comfy trousers/jogging bottoms</li>\r\n<li>Slippers</li>\r\n<li>Thin gloves</li>\r\n<li>Scarf</li>\r\n<li>Shoes/boots with a good grip</li>\r\n<li>Sports bra</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Other Stuff:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pyjamas</li>\r\n<li>Toiletries including toothbrush</li>\r\n<li>Sunscreen – high SPF</li>\r\n<li>Lipsalve/balm with SPF</li>\r\n<li>Aftersun/moisturiser</li>\r\n<li>Snowchains if driving</li>\r\n<li>Swimming costume/trunks</li>\r\n<li>Camera and charger</li>\r\n<li>Travel plug adaptor</li>\r\n<li>Speakers and headphones</li>\r\n<li>Books</li>\r\n<li>Magazines</li>\r\n<li>High energy snacks – chocolate bars/energy bars/nuts</li>\r\n<li>Any medication (including painkillers)</li>\r\n<li>Alarm clock</li>\r\n<li>Ear plugs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Luxuries:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Travel pillow</li>\r\n<li>GoPro</li>\r\n<li>Hairdryer</li>\r\n<li>Hair straighteners</li>\r\n<li>Cards/games</li>\r\n<li>Boot warmers</li>\r\n<li>Hand warmers</li>\r\n<li>Ankle/knee/wrist supports</li>\r\n<li>Deep Heat/muscle soaks</li>\r\n<li>Hip flask</li>\r\n<li>Handbag</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong></p>\r\n<p>As the weather condition is unpredictable in the Himalayan region, you need to be prepared at all times. A day can start sunny with clear skies and later become cold and windy at the high altitudes.</p>\r\n<p>Sometimes, it can rain and snow during the trekking period.  You need to remember that for a successful trekking journey, your physical comfort must be the first priority.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please note that these items listed above will vary according to the season, trek duration. Please remember that your luggage will be carried by the porter, but you need to carry a daypack on your own. We also suggest you pack only necessary items to keep the weight of your equipment to a minimum. Carrying a day pack only applies to the trekkers who take full package with us and those who take only guide they should bring the bag big enough to carry their own stuff. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us at your convenience.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; font-family: \'Arial MT\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Arial MT\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Arial MT\'; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Ghyun Himal I is the part of Mustang Himal sub range and is located in the Mustang District of Western Nepal.</span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; font-family: \'Open Sans\',\'serif\'; color: #676767; background: #F6F6F6;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; font-family: \'Arial MT\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Arial MT\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Arial MT\';\">The Dalai Lama calls Mustang the most preserved portion of Tibetan culture. Home to the kind and warm Lopa culture, it is a fascinating region of sky caves, remote glaciated 6000 meter peaks, and charismatic megafauna including truly wild yaks, snow leopards, and Tibetan wolves. We go into the region in the quiet season to explore Lopa culture and then to venture into the remote Tibetan borderlands to climb or ski 6000 meter peaks far from the beaten tracks.</span></p>', '3', NULL, 'ghyung-himal-skiing', 109, NULL, 'THORANG LA PASS', NULL, NULL, 'mustagataclimb-19-Zy8ih.jpg', '1725864113_f3977832-9038-4d75-9b8b-6fe5b0fd2c07-rZ7Yg.jpeg', '', 306, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, 'USD 4900', NULL, '2023-07-30 20:09:25', '2024-10-08 08:48:38'),
(140, 'MANASLU BASE CAMP', 'Worth it for the breathtaking scenery and the opportunity to experience the local culture.', '15 Days', '4,800m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Manaslu Base Camp is located in the Manaslu Conservation Area in Nepal. It is a popular trekking destination that offers stunning views of the Manaslu mountain range and the surrounding landscape. The trek to Manaslu Base Camp is a challenging one, but it is worth it for the breathtaking scenery and the opportunity to experience the local culture.<br /><br />The Manaslu region is home to several ethnic groups, including the Gurung, Magar, and Tamang people. These communities have their own unique cultures, traditions, and languages. The people of the Manaslu region are known for their hospitality and friendliness towards visitors.<br /><br />During the trek to Manaslu Base Camp, trekkers will have the opportunity to visit several villages and interact with the locals. They can learn about the traditional lifestyles of the people, their customs, and their beliefs. The villages along the trekking route are also known for their handicrafts, such as weaving, pottery, and woodcarving.<br /><br />The Manaslu region is also home to several Buddhist monasteries and temples. These religious sites are an important part of the local culture and offer a glimpse into the spiritual beliefs of the people. Trekkers can visit these sites and learn about the Buddhist philosophy and practices.<br /><br />In conclusion, the Manaslu Base Camp trek offers not only stunning natural beauty but also a rich cultural experience. Trekkers can immerse themselves in the local culture, interact with the friendly locals, and learn about their traditions and beliefs.&nbsp;</p>', '3', NULL, 'manaslu-base-camp', 110, NULL, 'MANASLU BASE CAMP TREK', 'MANASLU BASE CAMP TREK', 'Manaslu Base Camp is located in the Manaslu Conservation Area in Nepal. It is a popular trekking destination that offers stunning views of the Manaslu mountain range and the surrounding landscape.', 'img-4983-8A39e.jpeg', '1705761026_img-4985-2GmC0.jpeg', '', 262, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-07-30 20:22:30', '2024-10-16 03:34:03'),
(141, 'EVEREST 3 HIGH PASS TREK', NULL, '18 Days', '5,555m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>The Everest 3 High Pass Trek is an epic adventure in the Everest region. It takes you over three high mountain passes: Kongma La, Cho La, and Renjo La. You\'ll get to experience breathtaking views, visit remote villages, and witness stunning landscapes. It\'s a challenging trek, but definitely worth it for the incredible scenery and sense of accomplishment.</p>\r\n<p>The best time to do the Everest 3 High Pass Trek is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. These months offer stable weather conditions, clear skies, and moderate temperatures, making it ideal for trekking. The views are also stunning during these seasons.</p>', '2', NULL, 'everest-3-high-pass-trek', 111, NULL, 'EVEREST REGION', NULL, NULL, '90eed6a5-6586-4e28-8034-96b29aa3648e-IR3mJ.jpeg', '1705773561_img-4996-MT6Na.jpeg', '', 205, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2024-10-16 11:44:23'),
(144, 'UPPER MUSTANG WITH THORANGLA PASS', NULL, '17 Days', '5,416m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Upper Mustang is a fascinating region in Nepal that offers a unique trekking experience. Here\'s an overview of the Upper Mustang trek via Thorong La Pass:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Upper Mustang: Located in the Mustang District of Nepal, Upper Mustang is often referred to as the \"Forbidden Kingdom.\" It was restricted to foreigners until 1992, which has helped preserve its rich Tibetan culture and unique landscapes.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Thorong La Pass: While the Thorong La Pass is not directly on the Upper Mustang trek, it is a significant point on the popular Annapurna Circuit trek. The pass is located at an elevation of 5,416 meters (17,769 feet) and offers stunning panoramic views of the surrounding mountains.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Lo Manthang: The capital of Upper Mustang, Lo Manthang, is a walled city that was once the residence of the Mustang King. It is known for its ancient monasteries, traditional mud-brick houses, and vibrant Tibetan Buddhist culture.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Unique Landscapes: The Upper Mustang trek takes you through arid landscapes, deep canyons, and towering cliffs. You\'ll also encounter unique rock formations, such as the \"Demon\'s Gate\" and the \"Fairy Chimneys.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Cultural Immersion: The trek provides an opportunity to immerse yourself in the rich Tibetan Buddhist culture of the region. You can visit ancient monasteries, interact with friendly locals, and witness colorful festivals and rituals.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2', NULL, 'upper-mustang-with-thorangla-pass', 114, NULL, 'MUSTANG REGION', NULL, NULL, 'img-5029-m8475.jpeg', '1705772705_img-5028-cvs0F.jpeg', '', 146, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-08 07:13:05', '2024-10-16 03:27:52'),
(145, 'THREE PEAKS CLIMBING', NULL, '19 Days', '6189m', 'Spring', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<ol>\r\n<li>Island Peak (Imja Tse): Located in the Everest region, Island Peak is one of the most popular trekking peaks in Nepal. It offers stunning views of Everest, Lhotse, and other Himalayan peaks. The climb requires basic mountaineering skills and is often combined with the Everest Base Camp trek.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Mera Peak: Situated in the Khumbu region, Mera Peak is the highest trekking peak in Nepal, standing at 6,476 meters. It provides breathtaking panoramic views of the Everest region. The climb involves some technical sections, but it is considered suitable for climbers with moderate experience.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Lobuche Peak: Located in the Khumbu region, Lobuche Peak offers a challenging climb with rewarding views of Everest, Lhotse, Nuptse, and other peaks. It requires technical skills and previous mountaineering experience.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Peak 1: Island Peak (6,189m)</p>\r\n<p>Peak 2: Mera Peak (6,476m)</p>\r\n<p>Peak 3: Lobuche Peak (6,119m)</p>', '3', NULL, 'three-peaks-climbing', 115, NULL, 'Three Peaks Climbing', NULL, NULL, 'img-5022-zjcRU.jpeg', '1705829945_img-5044-MlL4N.jpeg', '', 201, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-08 07:34:54', '2024-10-08 09:37:07'),
(147, 'PISANG PEAK CLIMBING EXPEDITION (6,091M)', NULL, '20 Days', '6,091M', 'Spring', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Pisang Peak is a popular trekking peak located in the Annapurna region of Nepal. It stands at an elevation of 6,091 meters or 19,980 feet. Pisang Peak offers a thrilling climbing experience and stunning panoramic views of the Annapurna and Manaslu mountain ranges.</p>\r\n<p>The climb to Pisang Peak requires a good level of physical fitness and some previous trekking experience. The route to the summit involves steep sections, rocky terrain, and some technical climbing. It\'s important to have basic mountaineering skills and knowledge of using climbing equipment like ropes, harnesses, and crampons.</p>\r\n<p>The best time to attempt Pisang Peak climbing is during the spring (April and May) and autumn (October and November) seasons when the weather is generally more stable and the visibility is clear. These seasons offer the best conditions for climbing and enjoying the breathtaking views.</p>\r\n<p>The Pisang Peak climbing expedition usually starts from Besisahar and follows the Annapurna Circuit trekking route. Along the way, you\'ll pass through picturesque villages, lush forests, and beautiful landscapes. The climb itself is challenging but rewarding, and reaching the summit provides a sense of accomplishment and stunning views of the surrounding mountains.</p>', '1', NULL, 'pisang-peak-climbing-expedition-6091m', 117, NULL, 'Pisang Peak Climbing', NULL, NULL, 'img-5011-0wGQ7.jpeg', '1705768007_img-5012-RCnNF.jpeg', '', 97, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-08 10:42:06', '2024-10-11 18:13:42'),
(148, 'PACHERMO EXPEDITION (6,273M)', 'Pachermo where dreams meet the sky .', '19 Days', '6,273M', 'Spring', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Pachermo Peak is a popular trekking peak located in the Rolwaling region of Nepal. It stands at an elevation of 6,273 meters or 20,581 feet. The climb to Pachermo Peak offers stunning views of the surrounding Himalayan mountains, including Gauri Shankar, Melungtse, and Everest.</p>\r\n<p>The trek to Pachermo Peak usually starts from the village of Na in the Rolwaling Valley. From there, trekkers make their way through beautiful landscapes, including dense forests, alpine meadows, and glaciers. The climb itself requires basic mountaineering skills and experience, as it involves crossing crevasses and using fixed ropes.</p>\r\n<p>Reaching the summit of Pachermo Peak is a rewarding experience, offering panoramic views of the Himalayas and the Rolwaling Valley. It\'s important to note that proper acclimatization and physical fitness are essential for a successful climb.</p>\r\n<p>The best months to climb Pachermo Peak are generally during the spring (April and May) and autumn (October and November) seasons. During these months, the weather is relatively stable, with clear skies and moderate temperatures.</p>', '2', NULL, 'pachermo-expedition-6273m', 118, NULL, 'Pachermo', NULL, NULL, 'img-5010-6kt5Y.jpeg', '1705767815_img-5009-tAJCI.jpeg', '', 100, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-08 10:59:59', '2024-10-08 09:39:56'),
(149, 'HIMLUNG HIMAL EXPEDITION (7,126M)', 'Reach the summit of Himlung and touch the clouds.', '35 Days', '7,126M', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Himlung Himal is a beautiful mountain located in the Manaslu region of Nepal. It stands at an impressive height of 7,126 meters or 23,379 feet. The expedition to Himlung Himal offers a challenging and rewarding experience for mountaineers.</p>\r\n<p>The journey to Himlung Himal usually starts from the village of Koto in the Annapurna region. From there, trekkers make their way through diverse landscapes, including lush forests, picturesque valleys, and high-altitude terrain. The climb itself requires technical mountaineering skills, as it involves crossing glaciers, steep slopes, and potentially challenging weather conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Reaching the summit of Himlung Himal offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding Himalayan peaks, including Manaslu, Annapurna, and Dhaulagiri. The best time to attempt the Himlung Himal Expedition is during the spring (April and May) and autumn (October and November) seasons. These months generally offer more stable weather conditions, making it safer and more enjoyable for climbers.</p>\r\n<p>The Himlung Expedition is a popular mountaineering expedition in the Himalayas.&nbsp;</p>', '', NULL, 'himlung-himal-expedition-7126m', 119, NULL, 'Himlung Himal Expedition', NULL, NULL, 'img-5007-kRLUs.jpeg', '1705767515_img-5006-b3wnR.jpeg', '', 113, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, 'CHF 8\'000', NULL, '2024-01-09 05:42:21', '2024-10-16 13:19:02'),
(150, 'BARUNTSE EXPEDITION (7,129M)', 'Conquer Baruntse and write your own adventure story', '36 Days', '7,129M', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Baruntse is a stunning mountain located in the Khumbu region of Nepal. It stands at an impressive height of 7,129 meters or 23,389 feet. The Baruntse Expedition offers a challenging and rewarding experience for mountaineers.</p>\r\n<p>The journey to Baruntse typically starts from Lukla, and trekkers make their way through the beautiful landscapes of the Khumbu Valley. The climb itself requires technical mountaineering skills, including ice climbing, glacier travel, and high-altitude climbing techniques. It\'s important to have experience in using crampons, ice axes, and navigating through crevasses.</p>\r\n<p>Reaching the summit of Baruntse offers breathtaking views of the surrounding Himalayan peaks, including Everest, Lhotse, and Makalu. The best time to attempt the Baruntse Expedition is during the spring (April and May) and autumn (October and November) seasons, when the weather is generally more stable.</p>\r\n<p>The Baruntse expedition is a challenging and rewarding mountaineering adventure in the Himalayas.&nbsp;</p>', '3', NULL, 'baruntse-expedition-7129m', 120, NULL, 'Baruntse Expedition', NULL, NULL, 'img-5004-YTpbn.jpeg', '1705767109_img-5001-4w9Qy.jpeg', '', 102, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-09 05:51:37', '2024-10-16 07:46:15'),
(152, 'TAMANG HERITAGE TREK', NULL, '11 Days', '4,773m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>The Langtang Tamang Heritage Trek is a culturally enriching trek in Nepal that takes you through the traditional Tamang villages of the Langtang region. It offers a unique opportunity to explore the rich Tamang culture, witness their traditional lifestyle, and enjoy the stunning mountain views. The trek takes you through beautiful landscapes, terraced fields, and lush forests, providing an immersive experience in the local way of life. It\'s a fantastic trek for those seeking a blend of cultural immersion and natural beauty.</p>\r\n<p>Some of the traditional Tamang festivals include Lhosar, which marks the Tibetan New Year and is celebrated with music, dance, and feasts. Another important festival is Sonam Lhosar, which is celebrated to honor the Tamang New Year. Tamang Selo Festival is a vibrant celebration where traditional Tamang music and dance performances take place. Other festivals include Buddha Jayanti, Dumji, and Yartung. These festivals are a wonderful opportunity to immerse yourself in the vibrant culture and traditions of the Tamang community.</p>', '1', NULL, 'tamang-heritage-trek', 122, NULL, 'Tamang Heritage Trek', NULL, NULL, 'img-4971-bIKTr.jpeg', '1705758069_img-4969-jm8y8.jpeg', '', 117, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-09 06:22:17', '2024-10-16 03:12:51'),
(153, 'GANGLA PASS', NULL, '12 Days', '5,130m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>The Langtang Gangjala Pass is a challenging and adventurous trek in Nepal that takes you through the stunning Langtang Valley and over the Gangjala Pass. It\'s a less frequented route compared to other popular treks in the region, making it a great choice for those seeking a more off-the-beaten-path experience.</p>\r\n<p>The trek offers breathtaking views of snow-capped peaks, including Langtang Lirung, and takes you through diverse landscapes, including lush forests, alpine meadows, and rocky terrains. The highlight of the trek is crossing the Gangjala Pass, which requires some technical skills and equipment due to its steep and icy sections.</p>\r\n<p>Along the way, you\'ll have the opportunity to explore traditional Tamang villages, interact with the friendly locals, and learn about their unique culture and way of life. It\'s a challenging but rewarding trek for experienced trekkers looking for an unforgettable adventure in the Langtang region.</p>\r\n<p>The best time to trek the Langtang Gangjala Pass is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). During these seasons, the weather is generally clear, and the trails are more stable, making it easier to cross the trail.</p>', '2', NULL, 'gangla-pass', 123, NULL, 'Gangla Pass', NULL, NULL, 'img-4980-J1v8X.jpeg', '1705759108_img-4981-5tJUO.gif', '', 132, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-09 06:36:03', '2024-10-16 09:26:59'),
(154, 'GHANGCHENPO EXPEDITION (6378M)', NULL, '16 Days', '6378', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Ghangchhenpo, also known as Naya Kanga, is a popular peak for climbing in the Langtang region of Nepal. It stands at an elevation of 5,844 meters (19,173 feet) and offers a challenging yet rewarding experience for climbers.</p>\r\n<p>The climb to Ghangchhenpo requires mountaineering skills and experience, including the use of ice axes, crampons, and ropes. The route typically involves a mix of snow and ice climbing, as well as some technical sections. It\'s important to have proper acclimatization and physical fitness before attempting the climb.</p>\r\n<p>The best time to climb Ghangchhenpo is during the spring (April to May) and autumn (October to November) seasons when the weather is relatively stable, and the views are spectacular.</p>\r\n<p>Climbing Ghangchhenpo offers stunning panoramic views of the Langtang range, including Langtang Lirung, Dorje Lakpa, and Shishapangma. It\'s an incredible adventure for mountaineers looking to challenge themselves and experience the beauty of the Himalayas.</p>', '3', NULL, 'ghangchenpo-expedition-6378m', 124, NULL, 'Ghangchenpo', NULL, NULL, '589a38bc-a1c3-4712-acf9-27288efbe5c0-7dvBy.jpeg', '1705756719_589a38bc-a1c3-4712-acf9-27288efbe5c0-LUdyu.jpeg', '', 140, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-09 06:54:37', '2024-10-11 21:43:24'),
(155, 'NAYA KHANG', NULL, '16 Days', '5,844m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Naya Khang, also known as Ganja La Chuli, is a popular peak for climbing in the Langtang region of Nepal. It stands at an elevation of 5,844 meters (19,173 feet) and offers a challenging and thrilling experience for climbers.</p>\r\n<p>The climb to Naya Khang requires mountaineering skills and experience, including the use of ice axes, crampons, and ropes. The route typically involves steep sections, glacier crossings, and technical climbing. It\'s important to have proper acclimatization and physical fitness before attempting the climb.</p>\r\n<p>The best time to climb Naya Khang is during the spring (April to May) and autumn (October to November) seasons when the weather is relatively stable, and the views are breathtaking. However, it\'s crucial to check the weather conditions and consult with experienced guides for the most up-to-date information.</p>\r\n<p>Climbing Naya Khang offers stunning panoramic views of the Langtang range, including Langtang Lirung, Dorje Lakpa, and Shishapangma. It\'s an incredible adventure for mountaineers looking to challenge themselves and experience the beauty of the Himalayas.</p>', '2', NULL, 'naya-khang', 125, NULL, 'Naya Khang', NULL, NULL, 'img-9716-xqAWT.jpeg', '1705760086_img-4981-pyrO2.gif', '', 98, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, 'CHF 2\'500', NULL, '2024-01-09 07:00:29', '2024-10-16 07:36:51'),
(156, 'MANASALU CIRCUIT WITH TSUM VALLEY TREK', NULL, '23 Days', '5,160m', 'Spring/Fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n<li>World’s eight tallest mountain experience &amp; Manaslu Glacier</li>\r\n<li>Explore the secret Tibetan Buddhist land</li>\r\n<li>Experience the Nepalese and Tibetan mixture culture</li>\r\n<li>The trek introduces you to the antique monasteries, chortens, and gompas in the region.</li>\r\n<li>Walking between the borders of Nepal and Tibet</li>\r\n<li>Tibetan culture of Nuri people</li>\r\n<li>Diversified unspoiled ecosystems</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>This  trek offers trekkers  a combination of rich cultural heritage, unsurpassed beauty, and biological diversity. During this trip, one can see 10 peaks above 6500 metres such as Manaslu peak(8156), Larke Pass, Naike peak, Lamjung, Phungi (south face), Himlung, cheo Himal, etc and takes you into the majestic surroundings of the Ganesh Himal, Sringi Himal, and Boudha Himal ranges.  Tsum Valley Trek takes the visitors to the hidden valley of Tsum meaning “vivid” home to the direct descendant Tibetan people known as Tsumbas, the Tsum Valley is located to the east of Manaslu, on the border with Tibet.  Although the region lies within Nepal, the Buddhism influenced region is a world of its own.</p>\r\n<p>Manslu in in West – central Nepal is astounding with its fantastic mountain scenery spanning altitude from a few hundred meters to over 5000m. Home to a terrific variety of ecosystem, the Manaslu rute is one of the few true adventure experience. The trail links up with the eastern sector of the Annapurna circuit. Manaslu trek via Tsum valley around mighty 8163m high mountain of Manaslu and hidden valley of Tsum vally is unexpectedly poular among wilderness trekking knees. Though Manslu trek was opened in 1992 Tsum valley trek was released in 2008. This place is untouched by modernization where visitors can see immaculate state and remoteness and ancient ruins.</p>\r\n<p>These two combined trekking in this region is extra spectacular and culturally most mesmerizing area that rewards the trekkers to discover ultimate nature and cultural  heritage, unsurpassed beauty and a great bio diversity  and experience the mountain is Tsum valley and Manaslu. Also Tsum valley’s acquaintance with Tibet,natural beauty and pristine culture make the trekking more unique.  The breathtaking views of glorious Himalayan ranges will make you feel the typical Himalayan experience in this unique destination. Adventure Sherpa Tracks cordially welcomes you all for this amazing trip to Tsum Valley and Manaslu.</p>', '2', NULL, 'manasalu-circuit-with-tsum-valley-trek', 126, NULL, 'Manasalu Circuit with Tsum Valley', NULL, NULL, 'manaslu-circut-m5VUc.jpg', '1725460161_manaslu-circut-OEQLP.jpg', '', 126, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-09 08:58:51', '2024-10-16 11:32:22'),
(157, 'LARKEY PEAK CLIMBING', NULL, '16 Days', '5,160m', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>The Larkya Pass is a high mountain pass located on the Manaslu Circuit Trek in Nepal. It stands at an elevation of 5,160 meters (16,929 feet) and offers a challenging and rewarding experience for trekkers and mountaineers.</p>\r\n<p>Climbing the Larkya Pass requires good physical fitness and proper acclimatization. The route to the pass involves steep ascents, rocky terrain, and potentially icy sections, especially during the winter months. It\'s important to have prior trekking or mountaineering experience and be prepared with appropriate gear, including warm clothing, sturdy boots, and trekking poles.</p>\r\n<p>The best time to attempt the Larkya Pass is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. These months generally have more stable weather conditions and clearer views of the surrounding mountains.</p>\r\n<p>Reaching the top of the Larkya Pass rewards you with breathtaking panoramic views of the Manaslu region, including the snow-capped peaks of Manaslu, Himlung Himal, and Cheo Himal. It\'s a truly awe-inspiring sight and a memorable moment for any adventurer.</p>\r\n<p>While climbing the Larkya Pass is a challenging endeavor, it\'s important to remember that safety should always be the top priority. It\'s recommended to go with an experienced guide who can provide guidance, support, and ensure your well-being throughout the journey.</p>\r\n<p>Overall, climbing the Larkya Pass is an incredible adventure that offers stunning natural beauty and a sense of accomplishment. It\'s a must-do for those seeking a thrilling and memorable trekking experience in the Himalayas.</p>', '2', NULL, 'larkey-peak-climbing', 127, NULL, 'Larkey Peak Climbing', NULL, NULL, 'img-4966-BsotV.jpeg', '1705757669_img-4965-JeTK9.jpeg', '', 111, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-01-09 09:17:00', '2024-10-16 05:40:29');
