(212, 'Lobuche East Climbing with Everest BC & 2 passes trek', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n<li>Trek to the foot of breathtaking Everest, the world’s highest Mountain.</li>\r\n<li>Step inside and experience life as the “mountain people” in the heart of Himalayas</li>\r\n<li>Crossing 2 challenging 5000m passes: Renjo La,and Cho La pass</li>\r\n<li>Leave the crowds of the Everest Base Camp trek behind</li>\r\n<li>Stand at the shores of a chain of six turquoise, glacial-fed lakes</li>\r\n<li>Visiting Gokyo ri and gokyo lake .</li>\r\n<li>Hike along Ngozumpa Glacier, the largest glacier in the Himalaya</li>\r\n<li>Wonderful photographic opportunities</li>\r\n<li>Overwhelming experience of a lifetime adventure on Summit to labuche 6119m/20,070 ft) mountain.</li>\r\n<li>Great views of the Himalayan giants Amadablam, Lhotse &amp; Everest and Makalu</li>\r\n<li>Trekking and climbing experiences at one go</li>\r\n<li>Guided trip by Professional and Experienced climbing Sherpas who have already summited Everest</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 2, NULL, '', NULL, 'labuche-peks-LQf6X.jpg', NULL, '<p>Lobuche is a beautiful mountain which consists of two summits, East and West with heights of 6,119 m and 6,145 m respectively. ideal for those people who have done 4000m climbing  or have climbed in the Alps and are looking for their next expedition to tackle their first Himalayan Peak. This peak climbing includes some technical difficulties on quite steep snow slopes and one should possess some ice skills and use of fixed ropes for climbing along a steep, vertical and snowy trail.</p>\r\n<p>The peak of Lobuche East is reached by descending a marked notch and climbing steep snowy slopes to the top. On most occasions, the mountain is climbed on the summit ridge only as far as a subsidiary snow summit, south?east of the true peak and before the notch. This peak is identified as the false peak. Laurence Nielson and Ang Gyalzen Sherpa made the first ascent to Lobuje East on 25 April 1984 although there are possibilities that others have reached the summit before. But no records are available.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Adventure Sherpa Tracks</strong> offers Lobuche East Climbing  with proper acclimatize trip to two 5000 m passes  &amp; Everest Base Camp Trek  which provides excellent panoramic views of Everest along with other high mountains and gives you  trekking and climbing experience at one go .  If you are looking for climbing less crowed Peak than Island Peak, Then the best option would be Lobuche Peak with an ample experience and taste of Ice Climbing.</p>\r\n<p>The superb views from Mt. Lobuche make it one of the the most quintessentially-popular Himalayan treks, despite   it is a bit more challenging than Island Peak climb, it is equally rewarding. From the peak you get amazing views of Everest alongside Lhotse, Nuptse, Ama Dablam and Pumori and other several peaks.</p>\r\n<p>The best months to climb this peak is August through November &amp; March to june</p>', '', NULL, 'lobuche-east-climbing-with-everest-bc-2-passes-trek', 172, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'labuce-east-ff-1jxum.jpg', '', '', 40, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 02:49:35', '2024-10-17 03:37:43'),
(213, 'Saribung Peak Climbing', NULL, '26 Days', '6346 m', 'Spring /autonm', '6-8 hours', '2-10 pax', 'Tent /Tea house', NULL, '<ul>\r\n<li>The adventurous glacial and snow walk to the summit of Saribung Peak</li>\r\n<li>Venture into a remote part of Nepal that few travelers get to see</li>\r\n<li>Enjoy great views of Annapurna II, Himlung Himal, Gangapurna, and Tilicho Peak</li>\r\n<li>Witness a Tibetan-derived culture, with unique and colorful prayer stones and</li>\r\n<li>Enjoy the dramatic  mountain views of the high snow peaks and ancient villages</li>\r\n<li>Observe the medieval Tibetan culture in the hidden valle</li>\r\n<li>Experience spiritual peacefulness</li>\r\n<li>The remains of ancient Lo Kingdom at Upper Mustang and western and valley</li>\r\n<li>The amazing culture of people of Lo</li>\r\n<li>The off the beaten remote trial trek down to the wilds of Namta Khola Valley</li>\r\n<li>The adventurous glacial and snow walk to the summit of Saribung Peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Jeep', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p><strong>Saribung Peak Climbing</strong> journey, a newly explored peak climbing in Nepal, encompasses the remote regions of Nepal Himalayas – Jomsom, Mustang “Hidden Valley”, Nar-Phu Valley and many other landmarks of Damodar Himal in the company of majestic mountain sceneries, diverse cultures, and geographical variations. It is challenging and very popular trekking trail with beaten track and difficult pass.</p>\r\n<p>This <strong>Saribung peak climbing</strong>  is aimed at people who want a unique experience with an emphasis on trekking with a few days of climbing thrown into the mix. For mountaineering, it is easy to do Expedition but there are many passes with ice and creases in between the Damodar Kunda region and Nar-Phu valley.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Saribung peak</strong> is located in remote parts of Mustang region of Damodar Himal, close to the border of China (Tibet). Though the peak climbing journey is very much pleasant and easy at times the climbers have to cross the high passes like Saribung La over 5,600 meters and many other. At some sections, the trail even passes through the off-the-beaten-tracks and thereby results into the summit of Mt. <strong>Saribung</strong>. In over all, the panoramic mountain vistas form the top of Mt. Saribung, journeying through the rugged landscapes, and encountering the very much primitive culture of the region bring you an everlasting adventure experience in your life.</p>\r\n<p>Best Time for this Adventure is <strong>Sept – Oct, April – May   </strong></p>', '4', NULL, 'saribung-peak-climbing', 173, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img-1391-J8pxc.JPG', '', '', 11, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 02:53:34', '2024-10-16 11:24:56'),
(214, 'Ama Dablam Base Camp Trek', NULL, '2-10 Pax', '4800 meters', 'Spring /automn', '2-10 Pax', '2-10 Pax', NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n<li>Scenic flight to and from Lukla</li>\r\n<li>Trek to the foot of breathtaking Himalayas</li>\r\n<li>Step inside and experience life as the “mountain people”</li>\r\n<li>Visiting Tengboche Monastery and sherpa villages</li>\r\n<li>Experience Sherpa culture</li>\r\n<li>Trek into the heart of the famous Khumbu region of Nepal</li>\r\n<li>Visit picturesque Ama Dablam Base Camp</li>\r\n<li>Trekking with a Sherpa people</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Plane /Private Vechile', 1, 'NULL', '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Ama Dablam is regarded as one of the world’s most beautiful mountain.Trekking to the foot of this beautiful mountain features short and easy trekking in the Khumbu and Everest regions, taking you to the foot of beautiful towering  Ama  Dablam. Ama Dablam Base Camp trek is a leisurely trek to Everest region designed to take you to some of the prettiest Sherpa villages within easy walking distance with visits to Sherpa villages and Buddhist monasteries and Namche Bazaar Sherpa capital, with the ultimate objective of standing at the foot of the region’s most beautiful mountain.</p>\r\n<p>This trek allows you to trek to off the beaten track and well worth the walk for its rewarding views in the Everest Region.Ama Dablam Base Camp Trek  is  is best recommended for all those adventure &amp; mountain lovers who have limited time to stay in Nepal or who prefer comparatively easy walking trek in  Everest region with excellent Himalayan views.</p>', '2', NULL, 'ama-dablam-base-camp-trek', 174, '146800820-1727924220', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', 14, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 02:57:00', '2024-10-16 03:40:53'),
(215, 'Nar Phu Valley Trek', NULL, '2-10 Pax', '5,416m/17,770ft', 'Spring /autonm', '6-8 hours', '2-10 Pax', 'Tea Houses', NULL, '<ul class=\"list-highlights\">\r\n<li>Venture into a remote part of Nepal that few travelers get to see</li>\r\n<li>Enjoy great views of Annapurna II, Himlung Himal, Gangapurna, and Tilicho Peak</li>\r\n<li>Witness a Tibetan-derived culture, with unique and colorful prayer stones and</li>\r\n<li>Enjoy the dramatic  mountain views of the high snow peaks and ancient villages</li>\r\n<li>Observe the medieval Tibetan culture in the hidden valley</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Private Vechile', 1, 'NULL', '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>The Nar Phuy Valley Trek  is a real Himalayan wilderness experience that is as unforgettable as it is spectacular. This trek is an exotic trek to the remote Nar Phu Valley complete with high mountain passes, stunning Himalayan vista and heritage sites. Tucked between the more visited Annapurna and Manaslu regions, Nar Phu is a true hidden gem that offers trekkers a rare opportunity to explore unspoiled valleys that feature a mix of raw Himalayan nature and ancient Buddhist culture. The Nar Phu Valley trek only opened in 2003 and still remains a relatively little-trekked area. In fact, this hidden valley requires a special permit to enter.</p>\r\n<p>Nar Phu Valley Trek combined Annapurna Circuit is one of the most adventurous treks in the remotest parts of the Himalayas which features beautiful panorama along with diverse culture. While Nar Phu Valley is one of the least visited trekking routes, Annapurna Circuit is one of the popular trekking trails in Nepal  So, our Nar Phu Valley Trek combined Annapurna Circuit allows you to experience both the isolated and the crowded sides of the Nepal  Himalayas. This region has been only open to trekkers for 11 years now and holds centuries of untouched beauty.</p>', '2', NULL, 'nar-phu-valley-trek', 175, '957406110-1727924443', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', 12, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 03:00:43', '2024-10-16 07:40:07'),
(216, 'Tilman Pass Trek', NULL, '21 Days', '( 5320m/17450ft)', 'Spring /autonm', '6-8 hours', '2-10 Pax', 'Tent /Tea house', NULL, '<ul>\r\n<li>Adventurous Tilman Pass (5320m/17450ft)</li>\r\n<li>Organic Yak Cheese Factory</li>\r\n<li>Trek to the sacred Hindu lakes of Panch Pokhari, one of the highest altitude wetlands in the world</li>\r\n<li>Be awe-inspired by the massive south face of Langtang Lirung (7227m)</li>\r\n<li>Pass through stunning forests, high alpine meadows, and yak pastures.</li>\r\n<li>Varied vegetation and mixed landscapes.</li>\r\n<li>Experience the rich cultural exploration of the local people in the Himalaya</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Private jeep', 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>Tilman pass trek is one of the challenging, highest and difficult trekking passes between Langtang and Helambu region. It is one of the non touristy trekking trails. Tilman pass trek offers the best Himalayan views of Langtang, Ganesh Himal &amp; Rolwaling Himalayan ranges.Tilman Pass stands tall with an attitude of 5320m. It was named after the British adventurer and explorer H. W. Tillman (1898-1977) who explored the Himalaya in the mid-20th century. Tilman Pass is one of the toughest mountain passes of Nepal  that connects the Tamang valley of Langtang with the sacred lakes of Panchpokhari while featuring continuous views of the Himalayas including the Langtang Himal range and Jugal Himal range.</p>\r\n<p>Tilman pass trekking is less crowed for the trekkers who have entire desire of enjoying with nature in the remote area.Tillman Pass Trekking gives you different region Himalayan views, almost relaxing with High passes Himalaya range, living style of rural people and shares their culture.</p>', '4', NULL, 'tilman-pass-trek', 176, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '92c464d5-0729-4457-b13a-90c50b820b9e-g6uii.jpeg', '1728450138_a0d24f43-f170-4f0e-916a-a7443d58d564-SbVzu.jpeg', '', 12, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 03:04:37', '2024-10-16 09:39:05'),
(217, 'Makalu Base Camp Trek', NULL, '23 Days', '4,870m / 15,978ft.', 'Spring /autonm', NULL, '2-10 Pax', NULL, NULL, '<ul class=\"list-highlights\">\r\n<li>Complete the spectacular trek to Makalu Base Camp where few others have ventured</li>\r\n<li>See Everest from a unique angle, it’s eastern Kangshung face</li>\r\n<li>Gain views of eastern Nepal, as far away as Kangchenjunga</li>\r\n<li>Pass from green terraced farmland to glaciers and waterfalls</li>\r\n<li>Witness the rural life of Nepal’s distinct Rai and Sherpa culture</li>\r\n<li>Spot some of the rarest wildlife in Nepal, including the Red Panda</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 3, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>The spectacular trek to Makalu Base Camp has long been one of Nepal’s best kept trekking secrets. Closed to the outside world until the 1950s, when Eric Shipton first trekked into the region, it has remained relatively inaccessible and little-known except to a handful of keen trekkers; camping en route. Adventure Sherpa Tracks is  delighted to now be able to offer the trail to the foot of the world’s fifth highest peak. The Makalu Base Camp trek is a remote route that encompasses some of the best that Nepal has to offer — quiet trails, vibrant terraced farmland, rural cultures, rhododendron forests, rare wildlife and several 8,000 meter-plus peaks. For experienced trekkers who relish a challenge, this is a great trek with ample rewards.</p>\r\n<p>The Makalu Base Camp trek is an ideal trek for nature-loving trekkers who want to experience a variety of landscapes and cultures, as well as uncommon views of some of the world’s tallest mountains, including Everest.This trek  can be fairly challenging in some parts depending upon your level of physical fitness. Outstanding scenery of Makalu Base Camp Trek’s route significantly provides unique cultural heritage and incredible views of mountain peaks.</p>', '', NULL, 'makalu-base-camp-trek', 177, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'makalu-bc-OG6lt.jpg', '1728449942_makalu-bc-yCKNt.jpg', '', 11, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 03:11:10', '2024-10-12 08:55:49'),
(218, 'Manaslu and Tsum Valley Trek', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n<li>World’s eight tallest mountain experience &amp; Manaslu Glacier</li>\r\n<li>Explore the secret Tibetan Buddhist land</li>\r\n<li>Experience the Nepalese and Tibetan mixture culture</li>\r\n<li>The trek introduces you to the antique monasteries, chortens, and gompas in the region.</li>\r\n<li>Walking between the borders of Nepal and Tibet</li>\r\n<li>Tibetan culture of Nuri people</li>\r\n<li>Diversified unspoiled ecosystems</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 3, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>This  trek offers trekkers  a combination of rich cultural heritage, unsurpassed beauty, and biological diversity. During this trip, one can see 10 peaks above 6500 metres such as Manaslu peak(8156), Larke Pass, Naike peak, Lamjung, Phungi (south face), Himlung, cheo Himal, etc and takes you into the majestic surroundings of the Ganesh Himal, Sringi Himal, and Boudha Himal ranges.  Tsum Valley Trek takes the visitors to the hidden valley of Tsum meaning “vivid” home to the direct descendant Tibetan people known as Tsumbas, the Tsum Valley is located to the east of Manaslu, on the border with Tibet.  Although the region lies within Nepal, the Buddhism influenced region is a world of its own.</p>\r\n<p>Manslu in in West – central Nepal is astounding with its fantastic mountain scenery spanning altitude from a few hundred meters to over 5000m. Home to a terrific variety of ecosystem, the Manaslu rute is one of the few true adventure experience. The trail links up with the eastern sector of the Annapurna circuit. Manaslu trek via Tsum valley around mighty 8163m high mountain of Manaslu and hidden valley of Tsum vally is unexpectedly poular among wilderness trekking knees. Though Manslu trek was opened in 1992 Tsum valley trek was released in 2008. This place is untouched by modernization where visitors can see immaculate state and remoteness and ancient ruins.</p>\r\n<p>These two combined trekking in this region is extra spectacular and culturally most mesmerizing area that rewards the trekkers to discover ultimate nature and cultural  heritage, unsurpassed beauty and a great bio diversity  and experience the mountain is Tsum valley and Manaslu. Also Tsum valley’s acquaintance with Tibet,natural beauty and pristine culture make the trekking more unique.  The breathtaking views of glorious Himalayan ranges will make you feel the typical Himalayan experience in this unique destination. Adventure Sherpa Tracks cordially welcomes you all for this amazing trip to Tsum Valley and Manaslu.</p>', '', NULL, 'manaslu-and-tsum-valley-trek', 178, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'manaslu-circut-7s5MI.jpg', '1728449721_194775395-772438690109152-9096106868735133760-n-iUlGM.jpg', '', 8, 0, '1', '0', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-10-03 03:15:08', '2024-10-17 07:24:06');
