INSERT INTO `trip_reviews` (`id`, `trip_id`, `full_name`, `country`, `email`, `contact`, `rating`, `image`, `message`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(3, 131, 'Laura Schafer', 'USA', 'email2sherpa@gmail.com', '9860275519', 5, '1727894548.jpeg', '<p>I took my first trek to Nepal in Oct 2018 — it’s an absolutely amazing country/experience!! If you’ve ever wanted to go, I can highly recommend Adventure Sherpa Tracks &nbsp;— Lhakpa and his team are extremely knowledgeable and connected throughout the region. They provide porters, guides and fantastic service, taking care of all accommodations, food and support. I was extremely impressed and look forward to a future trip back to Nepal with this outfit!!!<br></p>', 1, '2024-07-30 12:27:32', '2024-10-02 18:49:26'),
(4, 145, 'Chris Begley', 'United Kingdom', 'email2sherpa@gmail.com', '9860275519', NULL, '1727894873.jpeg', '<p>Adventure Sherpa Tracks are a small trekking company based in Kathmandu and offer trekking and peak climbing itineraries in Nepal. They also include expeditions as well as providing bespoke packages to meet customer needs.<br>They tailor made the trip to meet my requirements and offered a very competitive rate compared to the less comprehensive itineraries offered by the mainstream online global adventure holiday companies.<br>The standard of service offered throughout the booking process was excellent and Adventure Sherpa Tracks were always prompt to answer the many questions I had.<br>The company director and guide Lhakpa G. Sherpa is a real gentleman and was fantastic throughout the trek, ensuring that everything ran smoothly for the whole trip.<br>The standard of accommodation and food was significantly better than I had expected based on a trip to Annapurna Sanctuary last year with one of the main adventure holiday companies – notwithstanding the ‘washroom facilities’, so set your expectations accordingly!<br>The only recommendation I would make is to allow more time for acclimatisation before going over Renjo La pass when approached from the west (clockwise direction).<br>I would not hesitate in recommending Adventure Sherpa Tracks for your next adventure in Nepal.<br>Many thanks<br>Christopher Begley<br>BSc (Hons) CEng FRAeS<br></p>', 1, '2024-07-31 08:17:59', '2024-10-02 18:48:12'),
(10, 194, 'Jim Keesling', 'USA', 'email2sherpa@gmail.com', '9860275519', NULL, '1727894156.jpeg', '<p>What a fantastic trip to Everest Base Camp with Adventure Sherpa Tracks in October 2017. Planning a trip to the Himalayas is a once in a lifetime thing for so many people and so so much easier if you use a tour guide like Adventure Sherpa Tracks. What a great choice to use them! The tour guide met me at the airport, took me to the Yak and Yeti hotel, a great hotel, then were with me throughout the adventure. It was so relaxing letting them handle the logistics throughout the trek including bunkhouses and making sure we climatized to avoid any health concerns. We also climbed Island Peak (6,000 meter/20,300 ft) and had a solid climbing guide. I loved this trip and will cherish it my entire life. I will likely plan a return trip and will team up with Adventure Sherpa Tracks!! 😎<br></p>', 1, '2024-10-02 17:48:36', '2024-10-02 18:38:38'),
(12, 194, 'Bre Mirynech', 'Canada', 'email2sherpa@gmail.com', '9860275519', NULL, '1727895836.jpeg', '<p></p><p>I don’t even know where to begin with all of the incredible things I have to say about this company. &nbsp;When I was looking into planning my trip for Island Peak, I contacted various companies and nothing seemed like the right fit. &nbsp;The day I messaged Adventure Sherpa Tracks, Lhakpa was super quick to respond and got back to me later that day with not one, but three custom itineraries to fit my objectives and budget. Its safe to say I was instantly blown away and so excited!</p><p>From there and for the rest of the planning, Lhakpa was amazing at communicating with me always. If I ever had questions, he always replied in an incredibly timely manner and made it all so easy for me.</p><p>The whole experience was phenomenal. Their communication, support, positivity, knowledge, all of it was incredible. I cannot recommend booking your trek or climb with this company enough. </p><p>Even after my trip was done, I stuck around Nepal with a friend to do the Annapurna Circuit without a guide. Lhakpa helped us book our transport to the start of the circuit. Throughout our trip he constantly checked in, offered us help and advice, and this was all while we weren’t even trekking with his company any more. </p><p>His kindness spoke volumes to me. He also made sure my friend and I had the most beautiful farewell the night before we left Kathmandu with a great dinner and some traditional Nepali dance performances. </p><p>I can’t thank Adventure Sherpa Tracks, Lhakpa and Chhiri enough for everything they did for me. My second time in Nepal was so incredible all thanks to them. I am forever grateful and will definitely be booking with them again in the future when I decide to try my hand at another climb.</p><br><p></p>', 1, '2024-10-02 19:02:37', '2024-10-02 19:04:33'),
(13, 195, 'Sophie La Canna', 'Australia', 'email2sherpa@gmail.com', '9860275519', NULL, '1727897521.jpeg', '<p>I can’t speak highly enough of Lhakpa and his company. I went for a solo trek in the lower mustang area in April. Lhakpa is a professional and experienced guide who was absolutely wonderful in helping me in all areas Of the trek, he listened to my needs (not doing too many kms per day!), my pace (slow!), he organised all accommodation and found guest houses that had an attached bathroom (and hot water!), which were clean and had delicious food (daal Bhat!!!). He knows the trail tracks even without a map, which I never would have wanted to navigate solo. Nothing is too much trouble for him and he sorts out anything you need with his lovely smile and positive nature (even when climbing big hills!). My goal for the trip was to slow down and immerse myself in nature, my journey/itinerary definitely met my expectations and more. I would not hesitate to recommend Lhakpa as I’m sure whatever you’re needs are he will design a fantastic itinerary for you and you will have the best time with him and his team. When I return I will be using Lhakpa again. He is a genuine Sherpa and shared amazing information to my many questions about Nepalese culture, I was so lucky to have had him as my guide. Thank you so much Lhakpa.<br></p>', 1, '2024-10-02 19:31:37', '2024-10-02 19:32:01'),
(14, 193, 'Ruben Baer', 'Switzerland', 'email2sherpa@gmail.com', '9860275519', NULL, '1727898021.jpeg', '<p>This autumn my Friend and I went on an expedition to Island Peak and Ama Dablam in the fabulous Khumbu Valley. It was an amazing experience and would have not been possible without the support of Adventure Peak Tracks. They helped us organising all required permits, connected us with an superb porter and provided a great base camp service! We were very flexible on our expedition and were able to take the time needed.<br><br>It was my first time in Nepal and I had such a good time and met many great people. Thank you all for your hospitality and giving me an unforgettable experience.<br><br>The team is very experienced and professional and know their area very well. I can really recommend them for your next trek and expedition in Nepal!<br><br>See you again!<br></p>', 1, '2024-10-02 19:40:02', '2024-10-02 19:40:21');
